California LA I guess
A random ass park
6:12 AM
Character: William [ Gay and seke ]
__________________________________
⠀
[] Why must I be the one?
I'd ask myself everyday.
You'd think as a time traveler [ in my definition, the ripper of the fabric of time ] that it'd be great living in such a carefree lifestyle. It isn't, really. I am no normal human which you can already tell by my hair and eye colour I was born with even though both by parents were brunettes [ and I can't remember their eye colour ]. But if I had to be honest it never does truly get boring and monotonous, everyday is a knew adventure. I won't go into depth about how I do this but I do it because I wanted to finish what my dad started, learning about the secrets of the mysterious world.
______________________________________________
⠀
William wandered about the time between the vintage years and the engineering casualties. He made a stop once he was in an area where it seemed to be no one around and set his his watch to '1785 of London England'. In the matter of seconds he'd rip a large hole in the fabric and step through to get to his destination. Technically William wasn't even a time traveler since not only can he travel through time but he could teleport. He could also do other astounding things.
[] All you have to do is run into William at the right second so you are taken with him to travel through time .w. so, yea. []
⠀

Comment: keut said "🌴 i was feeling a little low so i stepped aside to have some alone time in one of the seating areas on the 3rd level of the grand californian, and once everyone else had cleared out of the area except me, a security CM approached me and asked me to leave because it is apparently a hotel guest-only spot.  at the moment, i had been recovering from a few tears (sometimes you feel a little "it's my party and i'll cry if i want to", ya know) so this shook me up. she followed me to the bathroom. later, i decided to recover in the car & i walked past a group of guys who loudly questioned me about my outfit and whether it was dapper. i consider myself to be a relatively confident person, and these things really hit me when i was down, to say the least. i wanted to share to remind all of you that sometimes life isn't perfect, but there will always be people there for you to help pick yourself back up. Comment: mwepcot82 said "The 1958 addition of the #GrandCanyonDiorama painted by artist Delmer J. Yoakum necessitated a change in the rolling stock as well; instead of facing forward, the new flatcars' benches now faced right so that the passengers could better enjoy the scenes. The diorama, which includes taxidermic animals (the only ones in the park) in lifelike poses, is the longest in the world. Painted on a single piece of seamless canvas and representing the view from the canyon's south rim, the rear of the diorama measures 306 feet (93 m) long, 34 feet (10 m) high and is covered with 300 gallons (1,100 L) of paint in 14 colors.[5] Animals that are included in the diorama include mule deer, mountain lion, desert bighorn sheep, golden eagle, wild turkeys, striped skunk and porcupine. A 96-year-old Hopi chief, Chief Nevangnewa, blessed the trains on the diorama's opening day. The cost was US$367,000, and it took 80,000 labor hours to construct. The main theme of Ferde Grofé's "On The Trail," the third movement from his Grand Canyon Suite, is piped in through the train's sound system as it enters the diorama."

Comment: mz_poeticmoodsz_muslimah said "#YOU & #ME
I see a ME without YOU and wondered if you knew
there’d be a YOU without ME and that’s the way
you really wanted it to be.

I wanted there to be a YOU with ME that would
make up a WE and see how that would feel,
but alas, that’s not a vision YOU could see.

Were “we” not in the same space and time when it was
ME you would find as your needs itched so deep only I could
give the relief YOU claimed to seek… Or was that just ME?

Was it not YOU that said, in time just another one of
your repeated lines that we could be two lovers
Who could share the same space not just smile in each
other’s face,But yearn and live for each other’s embrace.

YOU said though it would take some time I should accept that
It’s better to dismiss never of the possibility of us being together

Always thinking YOU were ever so clever as you were,
to say it might happen but at some late date and that
I should wait but why I kept asking, “Should that be my fate? “

Really it was only ME that I’d see in my dreams on a
never-ending chase in a long and winding race to
some unknown future date of ME rushing to an open gate

Hoping to greet YOU in my arms but with looks forlorn
come to know that YOU were not there to share
your world forever more but only stopped by yet again
for another one of your “too short” visits.

Seems I was too blind to the fires & desires
that lived deep within my mind. And somehow
I knew in time YOU’d be the reason I’d come undone
Always struggling but also settling for
what resulted in only just a little bit of fun.

Envisioning the big picture I could see us framed on my
wall Proof that “we” were real and there was a YOU & ME
But DAMN! I’m just livid after all.

I guess the YOU that I saw with “ME” was never really a “we”.
Just wishful thinking it would be, a fantasy it seems.
And in the end I keep asking myself
Was there ever really a YOU & ME?
#poetry #art #epitome#of#Depth
by Dave O. Wallen (Heartache)
September 13, 2010©
The Essence Literary Art
www.Prosodigy.wordpress.com"

Comment: sister_manda said "The five best friends that anyone could ever have #disneyland #californiaadventure #goofy #thehappiestplaceonearth #regram"
Comment: mz_poeticmoodsz_muslimah said "#YOU & #ME
I see a ME without YOU and wondered if you knew
there’d be a YOU without ME and that’s the way
you really wanted it to be.

I wanted there to be a YOU with ME that would
make up a WE and see how that would feel,
but alas, that’s not a vision YOU could see.

Were “we” not in the same space and time when it was
ME you would find as your needs itched so deep only I could
give the relief YOU claimed to seek… Or was that just ME?

Was it not YOU that said, in time just another one of
your repeated lines that we could be two lovers
Who could share the same space not just smile in each
other’s face,But yearn and live for each other’s embrace.

YOU said though it would take some time I should accept that
It’s better to dismiss never of the possibility of us being together

Always thinking YOU were ever so clever as you were,
to say it might happen but at some late date and that
I should wait but why I kept asking, “Should that be my fate? “

Really it was only ME that I’d see in my dreams on a
never-ending chase in a long and winding race to
some unknown future date of ME rushing to an open gate

Hoping to greet YOU in my arms but with looks forlorn
come to know that YOU were not there to share
your world forever more but only stopped by yet again
for another one of your “too short” visits.

Seems I was too blind to the fires & desires
that lived deep within my mind. And somehow
I knew in time YOU’d be the reason I’d come undone
Always struggling but also settling for
what resulted in only just a little bit of fun.

Envisioning the big picture I could see us framed on my
wall Proof that “we” were real and there was a YOU & ME
But DAMN! I’m just livid after all.

I guess the YOU that I saw with “ME” was never really a “we”.
Just wishful thinking it would be, a fantasy it seems.
And in the end I keep asking myself
Was there ever really a YOU & ME?
#poetry #art #epitome#of#Depth
by Dave O. Wallen (Heartache)
September 13, 2010©
The Essence Literary Art
www.Prosodigy.wordpress.com"

Comment: mz_poeticmoodsz_muslimah said "'Uqbah bin 'Amir, may Allah be pleased with him, reported:

Allah's Messenger (may peace be upon him) one day went out and he offered the Prayer over the martyrs of Uhud just as the Prayer is offered over the dead. He then came back and sat on the pulpit and said: I will be the predecessor before you. I will be your witness and, by Allah,I perceive as if I am seeing with my own eyes my Hawd (River in Paradise) at this very moment and I have been given the keys of the treasures of the earth or the keys of the earth and, by Allah, I am not afraid that you might associate anything (with Allah after me), but I am afraid that you will be vying with one another (for the possession of) the treasures of the earth.

Chapter regarding grant of Ghuyub (Unseen) to Prophet (Peace be upon him) and of things which have to happen in future.

The hadiths on this subject are like a #vast #ocean, the #depth of which #cannot be #found and the #water of which #cannot #end. This is one aspect of his miracles which is "DEFINITELY KNOWN" We have many hadiths which have reached us by multiple paths of transmission (tawatur) which prove that the Prophet (Alayhi salaatu wa sallam) has been given knowledge of Unseen. It is narrated by Hudhayfa (radiAllaahuanahu) that the Messenger of Allah (Alayhi salaatu wa sallam) stood on his (Pulpit) and "HE DID NOT LEAVE OUT ANYTHING BUT EXPLAINED WHAT SHALL HAPPEN UNTIL THE LAST HOUR" Whoever remembered it remembered it and whoever forgot it forgot it.[Qadhi Iyaad's Ash-Shifa, Volume No.1, Page No. 206]
#Deen #Hadith #Sunnah #Salaf #Dawah101 #TheNobleQuran #Knowledge #Tawheed #Islaam"

Comment: littlearabiadistrict said "Enjoy the ‪#‎Kabob‬ at @elmahroosacafe!

According to Sevan Nişanyan, an etymologist of the Turkish language, the word kabob is derived from the Persian word "kabap" meaning "fry". The word was first mentioned in a Turkish script of Kyssa-i Yusuf in 1377, which is the oldest known source where kebab is mentioned as a food. However, he emphasizes that the word has the equivalent meaning of "frying/burning" with "kabābu" in the old Akkadian language, and "kbabā/כבבא" in Syriac language. Tradition has it that the dish was invented by medieval Persian soldiers who used their swords to grill meat over open-field fires."

Comment: micahmthenson said "|| Dreams Do Come True || Once upon a time there was a little girl, and this little girl had a dream to be something that didn't exist. She knew her that her dream was virtually impossible but that is why it is called a dream, it is an idea or vision of something wanted so terribly but it is completely out of reach. However even though years went by the dream it did not die. It was locked away in the deepest part of her innocent young hopeful heart. One day she decided to get a job at the happiest place on earth. Since she could not be exactly what she dreamed of being, she at least wanted to feel apart of the magical memories that she loved so much as a child. Once she went into the building she saw the first preview for the movie 'Princess and the Frog' At that moment her heart stopped! A dream that she had tucked away in the farthest part of her heart was now a reality. Not only was the princess her same skin color but the princess literally looked like a cartoon replica of the young girl. To tie this story all together, just because you have a dream that is impossible and others may laugh at what you cry out to God for, this does not mean it can not happen. Every single great innovator, visionary, or leader in history all had dreams and goals that were impossible and completely out of reach. But the moral of this story is if you have something in your heart do not give up on it, push in, try harder, and trust that God hears your prayers and sees the cry's of your heart. Because just like this young girl, her dream was impossible but one day her dream became a reality and she seized that moment the instant it became possible! Do not be discouraged, be hopeful, dream bigger, and know that one day you will have your hearts desire!  In the words of Mr. Walt Disney, "All our dreams can come true, if we have the courage to pursue them" -Live in Truth- 
Micah Henson

Comment: thelegendarylotus_commander said "Date:  15/02/27
Function:  Targeted Removal
Rating:  5/10

Let's start with the negative; you're trading 4/4 flyers with whatever you're targeting so time this card very carefully.  That being said, this card EXILES multiple creatures whenever you damn well feel like it.  This card is great for situations when you'd rather face off against 4/4 flyers rather than a Vorinclex or Prophet of Kruphix.  It doesn't exactly put you in a better position, just a more palatable one.  This works great with cards that can repeatedly return things to their owner's hands since tokens just disappear. 
#magicthegathering 
#mtg 
#commander 
#thelegendarylotus"

Comment: thelegendarylotus_commander said "Date:  15/02/28
Function:  Miscellaneous
Rating:  8/10

Grave Pact has been a powerhouse for years and it has been improved in two ways:  First and foremost it has flash with makes for some really painful ambush plays to really punish your opponents.  2nd the cost only requires BB to Grave Pact's BBB although the CMC has increased by 1.  Decks with finely tuned mana bases won't see the difference but everyone else will appreciate the lower black requirement.

#magicthegathering 
#mtg 
#commander 
#thelegendarylotus"

Comment: thelegendarylotus_commander said "Date:  15/02/28
Function:  Misc./Kinda sorta mass removal with impeccable timing
Rating:  3/10

I want to talk about this card in its best environment at its most power.  This card shines in monoblue or in the presence of Stormtide Leviathan.  You have to have access to flash with Winding Canyons or Teferi, Mage of Zhalfir because playing it on your turn gives the opponents the opportunity to replaying everything immediately after your turn with all the triggered abilities.  When it is played with flash it is almost comparable with Cyclonic Rift in terms of devastating reach.  If you have access to Deadeye Navigator no one will be able to have any creatures stick to the battlefield. 
#magicthegathering 
#mtg
#commander 
#thelegendarylotus"

Comment: thelegendarylotus_commander said "Date:  15/02/27
Function:  Targeted Removal
Rating:  5/10

Let's start with the negative; you're trading 4/4 flyers with whatever you're targeting so time this card very carefully.  That being said, this card EXILES multiple creatures whenever you damn well feel like it.  This card is great for situations when you'd rather face off against 4/4 flyers rather than a Vorinclex or Prophet of Kruphix.  It doesn't exactly put you in a better position, just a more palatable one.  This works great with cards that can repeatedly return things to their owner's hands since tokens just disappear. 
#magicthegathering 
#mtg 
#commander 
#thelegendarylotus"

Comment: thelegendarylotus_commander said "Date:  15/03/01
Function:  Commander/Targeted Removal
Rating: 4/10

For maximum flavor, play with gold sleeves, gold dice, an gold tokens.

Comment: thelegendarylotus_commander said "Date:  15/02/28
Function:  Miscellaneous
Rating:  8/10

Grave Pact has been a powerhouse for years and it has been improved in two ways:  First and foremost it has flash with makes for some really painful ambush plays to really punish your opponents.  2nd the cost only requires BB to Grave Pact's BBB although the CMC has increased by 1.  Decks with finely tuned mana bases won't see the difference but everyone else will appreciate the lower black requirement.

Comment: thelegendarylotus_commander said "Date:  15/02/28
Function:  Misc./Kinda sorta mass removal with impeccable timing
Rating:  3/10

I want to talk about this card in its best environment at its most power.  This card shines in monoblue or in the presence of Stormtide Leviathan.  You have to have access to flash with Winding Canyons or Teferi, Mage of Zhalfir because playing it on your turn gives the opponents the opportunity to replaying everything immediately after your turn with all the triggered abilities.  When it is played with flash it is almost comparable with Cyclonic Rift in terms of devastating reach.  If you have access to Deadeye Navigator no one will be able to have any creatures stick to the battlefield. 
#magicthegathering 
#mtg
#commander 
#thelegendarylotus"

Comment: thelegendarylotus_commander said "Date:  15/03/02
Function:  Miscellaneous
Rating:  6/10

I absolutely love this card; the title is so appropriate when you time this correctly.
I never cared much for Mindslaver unless you sacrificed it the same turn you played it which brings its total cost to 10.  I hate playing the Mindslaver and letting it sit around to be destroyed by other players and turning everyone against you out of paranoia.  The 8 CMC is better than Mindslaver's 10 for immediate use. Because it is a sorcery it can be copied so it can harm or help you.  This card is for patient, plotting masterminds who can wait for the perfect opportunity to turn someone's card against themself (Necropotence, Greater Good) or to gain an ally against their will. 
#magicthegathering 
#mtg 
#commander 
#thelegendarylotus"

Comment: thelegendarylotus_commander said "Date:  15/03/02
Function:  Miscellaneous
Rating:  4/10

This card is the epitome of a double-edged sword.  Just make sure your damage output is always higher than your opponents or else you'll be in big trouble.  The flash ability gives you a lot of reach because your opponents can't account for damage that they can't see on the battlefield.  This card is also amazing in conjunction with white protection spells like Righteous Aura or Solitary Confinement.  You can just sit pretty in one corner and watch the world burn. 
#magicthegathering 
#mtg 
#commander 
#thelegendarylotus"

Comment: thelegendarylotus_commander said "Date:  15/03/02
Function:  Miscellaneous
Rating:  6/10

I absolutely love this card; the title is so appropriate when you time this correctly.
I never cared much for Mindslaver unless you sacrificed it the same turn you played it which brings its total cost to 10.  I hate playing the Mindslaver and letting it sit around to be destroyed by other players and turning everyone against you out of paranoia.  The 8 CMC is better than Mindslaver's 10 for immediate use. Because it is a sorcery it can be copied so it can harm or help you.  This card is for patient, plotting masterminds who can wait for the perfect opportunity to turn someone's card against themself (Necropotence, Greater Good) or to gain an ally against their will. 
#magicthegathering 
#mtg 
#commander 
#thelegendarylotus"

Comment: thelegendarylotus_commander said "Date:  15/03/01
Function:  Targeted Removal
Rating:  8/10

This is a great card that rewards you for building up your supply of mana.  Instant speed exile is devastating to powerful decks because they generally contain powerful recursion cards to replay creatures from the graveyard.  Unless your opponents play with Pull From Eternity of Riftsweeper, your targets will remain gone for good.

#magicthegathering 
#mtg 
#commander 
#thelegendarylotus"

Comment: thelegendarylotus_commander said "Date:  15/03/02
Function:  Miscellaneous
Rating:  4/10

This card is the epitome of a double-edged sword.  Just make sure your damage output is always higher than your opponents or else you'll be in big trouble.  The flash ability gives you a lot of reach because your opponents can't account for damage that they can't see on the battlefield.  This card is also amazing in conjunction with white protection spells like Righteous Aura or Solitary Confinement.  You can just sit pretty in one corner and watch the world burn. 
#magicthegathering 
#mtg 
#commander 
#thelegendarylotus"

Comment: thelegendarylotus_commander said "Date:  15/03/03
Function:  Miscellaneous 
Rating:  4/10

If you have 3 or more targets in mind, Insurrection is almost strictly better in every way.  With that in mind, this is ideal for two targets choosing one would make this the same as Threaten (not powerful enough). To maximize the power of this card, you will need free-to-activate sacrifice outlets (Greater Good, Greater Gargodon, or Goblin Bombardent) to treat this as targeted removal with the added perk or being able to attack with your targets.  Its a lot of work but its red... #magicthegathering

Function:  Mana Acceleration
Rating:  6/10
As stage 1 ramp (0-2 CMC) this card is quite competent in getting you to possible 4 mana by turn 3 with and 3rd land drop.  It makes use of your turn 1 since you rarely have anything to do anyways.  Also, because it is a permanent, it makes a useful target for Sun Titan if you happen to speed it out.

Comment: thelegendarylotus_commander said "Date:  15/03/03
Function:  Miscellaneous
Rating:  3/10
The only way to get a lot of value from this card is to have a battlefield full of different creatures with ETB (enter the battlefield) abilities as well as sacrifice outlets to make use of the tokens before they exile.  You would have to copy at least two creatures with awesome triggered abilities to make this worthwhile.

This is only the beginning, and the future is bright! I can't wait to share more of my passion with you all. I appreciate all of you! If you are at #ExpoWest stop by Booth #2284, See You Soon! THANK YOU LOVES 😘"

Comment: andyvnguyen said "Sometimes I forget how lean I got at one point in my life. A #tbt to the first time I was able to achieve visible abs. I became obsessed with carving more and more fat off of my body and making it look as shredded as possible. I took pictures of myself every day, critiquing and picking at deficiencies in my body. I was tracking macros for every single thing that went into my body and kept cutting back and back until I nearly starved myself. I looked good, but at what cost? I was so infatuated with the idea that I was no longer the "fat kid" that I began to show the beginning signs of muscle dysmorphia, a real issue for people in the fitness world. I feel healthier now, happier now, and more knowledgeable now. I still track macros, manipulate my weight to an extent, but I am more focused on longevity and overall satisfaction with life rather than instant gratification."

Comment: andyvnguyen said "#tbt to the day I met Jackson. February 23rd, 2014. I didn't plan on adopting him, I was just warming up to visiting some dogs in foster homes because the dog I was going to adopt at OC Animal Care got snatched up before I got there!.. But that's besides the point. I had a few dogs selected from #petfinder and Jackson was the closest one to visit in Orange. I picked him to visit because I didn't know he was a chihuahua, thought he was some kind of mix. He looked interesting in the picture like a little fox (damn their potato camera and 0.01 megapixels). Archel and I stopped by the foster parent's home and saw a bunch of dogs, and then saw Jackson, the little Beagle colored chihuahua. He had just gotten stepped on that day (the foster parent apologized profusely) and wasn't as excited or jumping around. I pet him a little bit and held him (he was only 4lbs!) and then left the room while Archel talked to the foster parent and played with Jackson. I made a few phone calls to get some information tabulated such as age, adoption fee, shots needed, health issues, etc. While I'm on the phone, this little furry animal runs to me and jumps into my lap. Turns out, it was Jackson. The foster parent and Archel walked over and were just saying "Awwww!" I just said "damnit, he's mine now." He chose me. I took him home that day. We've been inseparable since!"

💌🌞🐝💧🙈I woke up 2 this 🌻🌊😋🍌🍯❤️
This morning I was craving an açaí bowl, but unfortunately I didn't have any frozen fruits so in substitution I gathered up some fruits👉 (1 mango, 1 banana, 1/2 cup of blueberries) threw them into a bowl, added 1/4 cup of granola, topped with bee pollen, drizzled agave, & splashed almond milk all over 👈😌 Not only was this a filling & scrumptious breakfast, it has a lot of nutrients to wake you up and help you get your day started, as well as keep you on the right heathy eating track. Comment: natiluglio said "Duas novidades muitooo legais, a primeira é completamente inovadora! Não sei se vocês sabem mas aqui está igual SP com problemas de agua! Mas algum gênio já achou algo que vai ajudar MUITOO! Cada descarga gasta 3.7 litros em media (aqui), então como diz ai.. PORQUE DAR A DESCARGA? Eles criaram um liquido 100% feito de plantas que neutraliza odores e muda a cor da água, ou seja, substitui a descarga! Imaginem QUANTAAAA ECONOMIA na conta, e pro planeta! Menos agua aqui 🚽, mais agua 🍹!! Ainda não chegou no Brasil e é caro aqui também mas isso mostra que temos alternativas, basta querer! A segunda novidade, que não é tão nova são estes saquinhos biodegradáveis feito de plantas.. Parece tão simples, mas insistimos em usar petróleo! A natureza nos da tentas plantas, folhas, grãos, mas o homem é interesseiro, luxuoso, ganancioso.. Enfim parece que é mais barato usar petróleo que fica a 2543km de profundidade, não é sustentável, logo mais, logo menos vai acabar do que usar alternativas mais naturais e boas para o ambiente! #capitalismo ! 
Mais novidades mais tarde.. Fiquei tão encantada ontem que não consegui nem postar 🙈🙈 #healthylife #fitfamily #amomuito #porummundomelhor"
